text:
Valdez, Reyes lead 25-member SEAG volleyball pool By Leif Sykioco (philstar.com)   12:24pm Rachel Anne Daquis, Mika Reyes, Alyssa Valdez and Jaja Santiago cracked the 25-woman training pool. 
MANILA, Philippines â€” The national volleyball team training pool is finally complete, less than five months before the 2017 Southeast Asian Games. 
Women's national team head coach Francis Vicente announced the 25-woman pool Tuesday at the weekly PSA Forum at the Golden Phoenix Hotel in Pasay, with 10 collegiate players and 15 club players forming the group. 
National University's Jaja Santiago, and De La Salle University's Kim Fajardo and Kim Dy are among the collegiate standouts. Dawn Macandili also made the lineup along with Ateneo's Maddie Madayag and Kat Tolentino. 
Perpetual Help's Lourdes Clemente, University of the East's Roselle Baliton, Kath Arado and University of Santo Tomas' Ria Meneses complete the collegiate standouts. 
Crowd favorites Alyssa Valdez, Mika Reyes, Rachel Anne Daquis and Dindin Manabat cracked the training pool. 
Three-time NCAA MVP Gretchel Soltones, Aby Marano, Jovelyn Gonzaga and Denden Lazaro also made the pool.   
Completing the pool are Gen Casugod, Maika Ortiz, Bia General, Aiza Pontillas, Myla Pablo and Elaine Kasilag. 
Of the 25 players, only 12 will make the final cut and will get represent the country in the SEA Games in Malaysia.
